, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88076270/1911-02-02/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=1"}, {"number": 2, "url": null}, {"number": 3, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88076270/1911-02-02/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=3"}, {"number": 4, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88076270/1911-02-02/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=4"}], "perpage": 1, "perpage_options": [25, 50, 100, 150], "previous": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88076270/1911-02-02/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=1", "results": "2 - 2", "to": 2, "total": 10}, "previous_resource": {"label": "Previous Issue", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88076270/1911-01-26/ed-1/?fo=json&sp=1"}, "related_items": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://library.nd.gov/statedocs/NDSU/AAE74220150924.pdf", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017381923/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2017381923"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["bangsund, dean a.", "williston (n.d.)", "north dakota state university. department of agribusiness and applied economics", "hodur, nancy m."], "date": "2015", "dates": ["2015"], "description": ["Rapid expansion in the petroleum sector has led to unprecedented growth in the City of Williston. Employment opportunities in the oil and gas industry and other associated sectors (e.g., residential and commercial construction) have attracted thousands of workers, fueling population growth, housing shortages and inflated housing costs. Further, rapid growth has strained existing infrastructure and the delivery of public services. Communities are struggling to manage the many challenges associated with rapid growth, as well as plan for future delivery of public services and gauge response to demand for housing and infrastructure. One of the most basic metrics used to gauge response and guide planning processes is population projections. Study objectives were to estimate the current service population of Williston and Williams County and develop a five-year service population potential. The service population includes long-term normal residents, others that may work in North Dakota and live elsewhere, and those that live in North Dakota temporarily. A similar effort was undertaken in 2012 and this research updates the previous estimates of the service population in Williston and Williams County."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-06-02T18:58:37.253Z", "group": ["catalog-split-04", "catalog", "main-catalog-split-04", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2017381923", "image_url": [], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "location": ["williston", "williams county", "north dakota"], "number": ["2017-09-01t09:33:52", "n922935075", "2017381923"], "original_format": ["book"], "partof": ["catalog"], "score": 34.45906, "shelf_id": "HB3525.N9 H63 2015", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["petroleum industry and trade", "williston (n.d.)", "population", "williams county", "statistics", "population policy", "williams county (n.d.)", "oil industry workers", "population forecasting", "infrastructure (economics)", "williston", "social aspects", "north dakota", "economic aspects"], "timestamp": "2023-07-07T23:17:05.056Z", "title": "Service population estimates for city of Williston", "type": ["text"], "url": "//lccn.loc.gov/2017381923"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2017381323/", "http://library.nd.gov/statedocs/NDSUExtensionService/AAE70720160311.pdf", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2017381323", "http://purl.umn.edu/157412"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["bangsund, dean a.", "north dakota state university. department of agribusiness and applied economics", "hodur, nancy m."], "date": "2013", "dates": ["2013"], "description": ["Rapid expansion in the petroleum sector has led to unprecedented growth in the City of Williston. Employment opportunities in the oil and gas industry and other associated sectors (e.g., residential and commercial construction) has attracted thousands of workers fueling population growth, housing shortages and inflated housing costs. Further, rapid growth has strained existing infrastructure and the delivery of public services. Communities are struggling to manage the many challenges associated with rapid growth as well as plan for future delivery of public services and gauge response to demand for housing and infrastructure. One of the most  basic metrics used to gauge response and guide planning processes is population projections. Study objectives were to estimate the current service population of Williston and Williams County and develop a five-year service population projection. The service population includes long-term normal residents, others that may work in North Dakota and live elsewhere, and those that live in North Dakota temporarily."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-06-02T22:47:23.198Z", "group": ["catalog-split-14", "catalog", "main-catalog-split-14", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2017381323", "image_url": [], "index": 3, "language": ["english"], "location": ["williston", "williams county", "north dakota"], "number": ["2018-04-28t12:04:02", "2017381323", "n945553349"], "original_format": ["book"], "partof": ["catalog"], "score": 34.45906, "shelf_id": "HB3525.N9 H625 2013", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["williston (n.d.)", "population", "williams county", "williams county (n.d.)", "population forecasting", "employment forecasting", "williston", "north dakota"], "timestamp": "2023-07-10T14:43:59.277Z", "title": "Population estimates for city of Williston", "type": ["text"], "url": "//lccn.loc.gov/2017381323"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/fsa/item/2017780839/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017780839/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2017780839/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/fsa.8b20083", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/fsa.8b20083/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2017780839"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1937-01-01", "dates": ["1937"], "description": ["1 negative : safety ; 3 1/4 x 4 1/4 inches or smaller